    "is_generated": false,
    "segments": [
      {
        "start": 0.2,
        "duration": 1.5,
        "text": "- [Speaker] Wordsmiths all aboard."
      },
      {
        "start": 1.7,
        "duration": 3.3,
        "text": "Train to vocabulary city,\nmaking stops of prefixed gardens"
      },
      {
        "start": 5.0,
        "duration": 1.4,
        "text": "and Grand Root Central."
      },
      {
        "start": 6.4,
        "duration": 1.7,
        "text": "Chew, chew!"
      },
      {
        "start": 8.1,
        "duration": 2.1,
        "text": "What we're gonna do in this\nvideo is break some words down"
      },
      {
        "start": 10.2,
        "duration": 4.5,
        "text": "into parts so you can recognize\nthose parts in other words."
      },
      {
        "start": 14.7,
        "duration": 3.3,
        "text": "The words we're working on\nin this video are adapt,"
      },
      {
        "start": 18.0,
        "duration": 2.5,
        "text": "collaborate, and criticize."
      },
      {
        "start": 20.5,
        "duration": 1.4,
        "text": "I'll give you some definitions"
      },
      {
        "start": 21.8,
        "duration": 2.2,
        "text": "and then we'll break these words down."
      },
      {
        "start": 24.0,
        "duration": 3.7,
        "text": "Adapt is a verb that means\nto change your behavior"
      },
      {
        "start": 27.7,
        "duration": 2.8,
        "text": "or ideas in response to a new situation"
      },
      {
        "start": 30.6,
        "duration": 3.0,
        "text": "or to change something, to\nuse it in a different way."
      },
      {
        "start": 33.6,
        "duration": 3.0,
        "text": "There's also the noun form\nadaptation, which is the process"
      },
      {
        "start": 36.5,
        "duration": 3.0,
        "text": "of changing, or when you\nmake a book into a movie,"
      },
      {
        "start": 39.6,
        "duration": 1.6,
        "text": "that's another kind of adaptation."
      },
      {
        "start": 41.1,
        "duration": 2.0,
        "text": "You're changing a story from one medium"
      },
      {
        "start": 43.1,
        "duration": 1.9,
        "text": "to another.\nTo collaborate,"
      },
      {
        "start": 45.1,
        "duration": 3.4,
        "text": "another verb with someone is\nto work together with them"
      },
      {
        "start": 48.5,
        "duration": 2.4,
        "text": "and to criticize something is"
      },
      {
        "start": 50.8,
        "duration": 2.9,
        "text": "to judge something's\nqualities, whether good or bad,"
      },
      {
        "start": 53.8,
        "duration": 1.5,
        "text": "or to point out flaws."
      },
      {
        "start": 55.3,
        "duration": 3.9,
        "text": "Okay, back to adapt for word parts time."
      },
      {
        "start": 59.2,
        "duration": 2.6,
        "text": "Adapt has two parts we\nwanna pay attention to."
      },
      {
        "start": 61.9,
        "duration": 3.4,
        "text": "There's our old friend\nadd, which means on or to,"
      },
      {
        "start": 65.2,
        "duration": 3.6,
        "text": "and then there's this other\npart apt from the Latin aptare,"
      },
      {
        "start": 68.9,
        "duration": 2.1,
        "text": "meaning to join, to fit."
      },
      {
        "start": 71.0,
        "duration": 2.4,
        "text": "So something that is adapted is fit"
      },
      {
        "start": 73.4,
        "duration": 5.0,
        "text": "for some new purpose changed\nto join up with something."
      },
      {
        "start": 78.5,
        "duration": 2.4,
        "text": "Let's look at some other English\nwords that use this route."
      },
      {
        "start": 80.9,
        "duration": 3.8,
        "text": "We use the English word apt\njust on its own APT like that"
      },
      {
        "start": 84.7,
        "duration": 4.3,
        "text": "to mean appropriate like this\ntuxedo is apt for the occasion"
      },
      {
        "start": 89.1,
        "duration": 1.5,
        "text": "of a fancy dinner party."
      },
      {
        "start": 90.6,
        "duration": 3.8,
        "text": "Aptitude is being good at something,"
      },
      {
        "start": 94.4,
        "duration": 2.5,
        "text": "having abilities appropriate\nfor the situation."
      },
      {
        "start": 96.9,
        "duration": 2.5,
        "text": "Inapt meaning not apt, not appropriate,"
      },
      {
